<subSubSection id="C326E0F8A64F221438EB3C620F392E71" lastPageId="11" lastPageNumber="94" pageId="10" pageNumber="93" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8B83B373A64F221538EB3C620A982818" blockId="10.[189,416,1810,1837]" box="[189,416,1810,1837]" pageId="10" pageNumber="93">
<emphasis id="B9486F61A64F221538EB3C620A0E2819" bold="true" box="[189,310,1810,1836]" pageId="10" pageNumber="93">Diagnosis</emphasis>
(female)
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B83B373A64F221438EB3C310F392E71" blockId="10.[186,1399,1856,2025]" lastBlockId="11.[187,1398,265,325]" lastPageId="11" lastPageNumber="94" pageId="10" pageNumber="93">
Body length 3.0–4.0 mm; antenna as long as body, F15 length 2.0 × its width (
<figureCitation id="1307AFF6A64F22153C7A3C310FB0286E" box="[1068,1160,1856,1883]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="12.[189,232,1963,1989]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,808,1925]" captionTargetId="figure-119@12.[189,1398,808,1925]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="Fig. 5. Microplitis eremitus Reinhard, 1880, ♀, TMUC-HBMMP0017. A. Habitus, lateral view.B. Head, dorsal view. C. Mesosoma, dorsal view. D. Fore wing. E. Hind wing. F. Metasoma, dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4690340" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4690340/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="93">Fig. 5A</figureCitation>
); anteromesoscutum rugose and rugulose; notauli well defined by rugosity; mesoscutellar disc coriaceous to rugulose (
<figureCitation id="1307AFF6A64F221538903CF70A1D2897" box="[198,293,1927,1954]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="12.[189,232,1963,1989]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,808,1925]" captionTargetId="figure-119@12.[189,1398,808,1925]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="Fig. 5. Microplitis eremitus Reinhard, 1880, ♀, TMUC-HBMMP0017. A. Habitus, lateral view.B. Head, dorsal view. C. Mesosoma, dorsal view. D. Fore wing. E. Hind wing. F. Metasoma, dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4690340" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4690340/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="93">Fig. 5C</figureCitation>
); pterostigma length 2.5 × its width; vein R1 shorter than pterostigma (i.e., vein R1 longer than pterostigma half); 1 
<superScript id="7C491E3BA64F221539893CDA0AD2288D" attach="left" box="[479,490,1962,1976]" fontSize="6" pageId="10" pageNumber="93">st</superScript>
discal cell length 1.0–1.1 × its width; vein 1CUb 2.0 × as long as vein 1CUa (
<figureCitation id="1307AFF6A64F221538903CBE0A1D28DC" box="[198,293,1998,2025]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="12.[189,232,1963,1989]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,808,1925]" captionTargetId="figure-119@12.[189,1398,808,1925]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="Fig. 5. Microplitis eremitus Reinhard, 1880, ♀, TMUC-HBMMP0017. A. Habitus, lateral view.B. Head, dorsal view. C. Mesosoma, dorsal view. D. Fore wing. E. Hind wing. F. Metasoma, dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4690340" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4690340/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="93">Fig. 5D</figureCitation>
); T1 length 1.5–1.6 × its maximum width, T1 more or less broadening posteriorly (
<figureCitation id="1307AFF6A64F22153D583CBE0E5228DC" box="[1294,1386,1998,2025]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="12.[189,232,1963,1989]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,808,1925]" captionTargetId="figure-119@12.[189,1398,808,1925]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="Fig. 5. Microplitis eremitus Reinhard, 1880, ♀, TMUC-HBMMP0017. A. Habitus, lateral view.B. Head, dorsal view. C. Mesosoma, dorsal view. D. Fore wing. E. Hind wing. F. Metasoma, dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4690340" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4690340/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="93">Fig. 5F</figureCitation>
). Colour: body black; antenna, tegula and legs reddish yellow or yellow exception of dark brown metacoxa, metatibia and a dark spot at apical metafemur; pterostigma dark brown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
